        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37539",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=smoku",
                        "name": "smoku",
                        "displayName": "Tomasz Sterna",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here's a patch that fixes this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=smoku",
                        "name": "smoku",
                        "displayName": "Tomasz Sterna",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-10T12:33:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-10T12:33:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37546",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in trunk",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-10T14:48:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-11T06:14:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37547",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=smoku",
                        "name": "smoku",
                        "displayName": "Tomasz Sterna",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "User named 'thomas' already merged my patch in r20180 not mentioning this bug in the commit.\r\n\r\nWas that you?\r\n If so, why don't you just admit that you merged my patch to SVN, instead of pretending, that the bug was \"already fixed\"?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n$ svn log -c20180 library\/Zend\/\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nr20180 | thomas | 2010-01-10 21:43:25 +0100 (nie) | 3 linie\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[GENERIC] Zend_Validate:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n- fixed wrong messages\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n\r\n$ svn diff -c20180 library\/Zend\/ | head -n 20\r\n\r\nIndex: library\/Zend\/Validate\/NotEmpty.php\r\n\r\n===================================================================\r\n\r\n--- library\/Zend\/Validate\/NotEmpty.php\t(wersja 20179)\r\n\r\n+++ library\/Zend\/Validate\/NotEmpty.php\t(wersja 20180)\r\n\r\n@@ -164,7 +164,7 @@\r\n\r\n         if ($type >= self::SPACE) {\r\n\r\n             $type -= self::SPACE;\r\n\r\n             if (is_string($value) && (preg_match('\/^\\s+$\/s', $value))) {\r\n\r\n-                $this->_error(self::INVALID);\r\n\r\n+                $this->_error(self::IS_EMPTY);\r\n\r\n                 return false;\r\n\r\n             }\r\n\r\n         }\r\n\r\n@@ -173,7 +173,7 @@\r\n\r\n         if ($type >= self::NULL) {\r\n\r\n             $type -= self::NULL;\r\n\r\n             if (is_null($value)) {\r\n\r\n-                $this->_error(self::INVALID);\r\n\r\n+                $this->_error(self::IS_EMPTY);\r\n\r\n                 return false;\r\n\r\n[...]",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=smoku",
                        "name": "smoku",
                        "displayName": "Tomasz Sterna",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-10T15:40:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-10T15:40:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37551",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm in several online forums.\r\n\r\nSometimes I fix things when they are mentioned within a forum without raising an issue myself. And sometimes it collidates with another user reporting the same issue. \r\n\r\nAs there is only one solution for this problem, by using the correct constant, I would not be too strict in the wording \"my patch\". Other people come to the same conclusion without looking into your patch.\r\n\r\nYou may also have noted that email delivery for issues is delayed. The time this issue was sent to me, the fix was already committed.\r\n\r\nI'm sorry when such a situation is problematic for you. When you want I could wait some weeks in future before fixing things which are mentioned to me in a public discussion. :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-10T23:17:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-10T23:17:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37552",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=smoku",
                        "name": "smoku",
                        "displayName": "Tomasz Sterna",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Do you really expect me to believe that accidentally both two of my issues reported within an hour was \"already fixed\" with no other commits within a week, just these two just after the bug reports? And you are so busy, that you do not remember what exactly happened few hours ago and need to be speculative with \"sometimes\".\r\n\r\nI do not really care about giving credit for a few-liner patch.\r\nWhat struck me is the bizarre attitude of not admitting \"yes, there was a bug\" and pretending that the reports were invalid in a first place.\r\n\r\nYou just lost more than one user - I will discourage every person asking my advice and reading my blog from using ZF, because your development methods are doubtful and not transparent. EOT",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=smoku",
                        "name": "smoku",
                        "displayName": "Tomasz Sterna",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-10T23:52:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-10T23:52:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37561",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There were 40 commits within the last week by me, not only 2.\r\nAnd yes I am busy in my sparetime on sunday at home.\r\n\r\nNo one said that this report is invalid. I just said \"probably fixed in trunk\". The issue itself is marked as \"fixed\" and not as \"not an issue\" or \"incomplete\". In my eyes \"fixed\" is the proper status.\r\n\r\nAnd there is also a changeset connected to this issue which tests this behaviour.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-11T06:14:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-11T06:14:04.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
